    "Unknown": "Or, as it is in the Hebrew, word for word, upon the word of truth , &c.; which may seem best to suit with the foregoing words, which according to the Hebrew are, prosper thou, ride thou , and then immediately follows, upon the Word of truth , &c., to wit, the gospel; which is oft called truth, as Joh_8:32 Col_1:5, &c., and the word of truth , Eph_1:13; and may no less truly be called the word of meekness, because it is not delivered with terror, as the law was at Sinai, but meekly and sweetly by Christ, and by his ministers, Mat_21:5 2Ti_2:25; and the word of righteousness , because it brings in everlasting righteousness, Dan_9:24, and strongly obligeth and exciteth all men to the practice of righteousness and holiness. And so the gospel is compared to a horse or chariot, upon which Christ is said to ride, when the gospel is preached, and carried about from place to place, Rev_19:"
